02:25.879 --> 02:28.447
(Panting)

02:30.550 --> 02:32.718
(All) Mooney!

02:32.720 --> 02:34.286
(Man) Where you at, Mooney?

02:34.288 --> 02:37.623
(All) Mooney! Mooney!

02:37.625 --> 02:39.858
(Banging and pounding)

02:39.860 --> 02:43.862
Hey, don't drop your wad, you get spied on in the shower.

02:43.864 --> 02:44.496
Do it.

02:44.498 --> 02:45.697
Just do whatever faggy shit you want

02:45.699 --> 02:50.235
with your Cub Scout buddies, but keep the fuck away from us!

02:52.906 --> 02:54.606
What's that? I can't hear you.

02:54.608 --> 02:56.808
Don't give us that shit, you fucking liar.

02:56.810 --> 02:57.543
I wasn't spying.

02:57.545 --> 02:59.778
What were you doing then? Were you taking a dump?

02:59.780 --> 03:01.180
'Cause that's what toilets are for, man.

03:01.182 --> 03:02.481
It doesn't smell like he was taking a dump.

03:02.483 --> 03:04.383
Does it smell like he was taking a dump?

03:04.385 --> 03:07.219
Nah, man, someone needs to give this motherfucker

03:07.221 --> 03:07.920
a shitting lesson, huh?

03:07.922 --> 03:09.354
Oh, is that... is that what it is?

03:09.356 --> 03:11.790
Mooney, you need a lesson in potty training?

03:11.792 --> 03:14.660
Mooney, you're in luck 'cause I gotta go.

03:14.662 --> 03:17.196
Oh, yeah.

03:17.198 --> 03:19.565
(Chatter)

03:23.369 --> 03:25.804
Anybody else gotta go, huh?

03:25.806 --> 03:26.939
Who the fuck is Jamie Marks?

03:26.941 --> 03:31.944
(Aaron) Jamie Marks, he was... he was in your homeroom, right?

03:31.946 --> 03:33.378
Yeah.

03:33.380 --> 03:35.914
Did... did he have red hair?

03:35.916 --> 03:37.849
Nope.

03:37.851 --> 03:38.517
Wait.

03:38.519 --> 03:41.620
Was Jamie Marks a boy or a girl?

03:41.622 --> 03:42.921
It's a boy, you moron.

03:42.923 --> 03:45.557
Jamie Marks is that kid with the... the glasses

03:45.559 --> 03:48.493
and the... the... the Boy Scouts shirt.

03:48.495 --> 03:49.761
That's him, right?

03:49.763 --> 03:51.330
Mooney Marks.

03:51.332 --> 03:53.532
Told you.

03:53.534 --> 03:54.766
Oh, you know what I heard?

03:54.768 --> 03:57.669
I heard they found him without his eyeballs.

03:57.671 --> 03:58.770
I mean, like, seriously.

03:58.772 --> 04:00.939
And he was raped.

04:09.515 --> 04:11.750
(Mr. Motes) Yes, Elizabeth.

04:11.752 --> 04:14.853
Aren't we gonna talk about what's happened?

04:19.325 --> 04:21.293
Okay.

04:21.295 --> 04:22.694
Fine.

04:22.696 --> 04:25.631
Let's talk about what's happened.

04:26.266 --> 04:29.501
Who wants to talk about Mooney Marks?

04:29.503 --> 04:31.303
Do you, Elizabeth?

04:31.305 --> 04:33.372
You were a good friend of his?

04:33.539 --> 04:37.476
How did it make you feel when you learned he was gone?

04:39.846 --> 04:41.747
Hmm? Anyone?

04:42.048 --> 04:44.916
Should we talk about all those fond memories

04:44.918 --> 04:47.286
we have of Jamie?

04:47.288 --> 04:50.422
How everyone thought he was such a great guy?

04:51.658 --> 04:53.959
Who knew him?

04:53.961 --> 04:56.061
Gregory?

04:56.063 --> 04:57.963
Huh?

04:57.965 --> 04:59.731
Belinda.

05:01.000 --> 05:02.501
Eric.

05:03.469 --> 05:04.803
Anyone.

05:08.374 --> 05:09.541
Now...

05:09.543 --> 05:12.477
I think it's awful what's happened.

05:12.479 --> 05:12.911
I do.

05:12.913 --> 05:14.746
And if any of you wanna stay after class

05:14.748 --> 05:18.517
and discuss it, please feel free to do so.

05:18.851 --> 05:23.422
But right now, I think we should get back to work.

05:24.657 --> 05:30.862
♪♪ (Soft music)

06:12.905 --> 06:14.940
What are you doing here?

06:18.411 --> 06:20.479
Visiting.

06:22.115 --> 06:24.483
What are you doing here?

06:27.887 --> 06:30.122
You don't have to leave.

06:34.827 --> 06:36.495
It smells good.

06:39.899 --> 06:42.801
So do you really collect rocks?

06:44.504 --> 06:45.404
Yeah.

06:45.406 --> 06:47.406
Rocks are the best.

06:53.846 --> 06:56.114
He was in my homeroom.

07:05.625 --> 07:08.593
Down there is where I found him.

07:12.565 --> 07:15.033
He looked so scared.

07:20.640 --> 07:21.973
You're Adam.

07:24.043 --> 07:25.510
Gracie.

07:27.580 --> 07:28.847
I know your older brother...

07:28.849 --> 07:30.715
Unfortunately.

07:36.956 --> 07:39.124
You should come by tomorrow...

07:39.126 --> 07:40.959
And see my collection.

07:40.961 --> 07:43.728
My parents will be at marriage counseling.

07:55.708 --> 08:02.113
♪♪ (Soft music)

08:34.780 --> 08:36.715
(Linda) How was practice?

08:36.717 --> 08:38.283
(Adam) It's all right.

08:38.683 --> 08:42.220
I'm gonna go down to The Landing for a bit, okay?

08:42.222 --> 08:43.188
Just for a quick drink.

08:43.190 --> 08:46.057
I won't be late, I promise.

08:46.059 --> 08:47.893
Have fun.

08:47.895 --> 08:49.594
Thank you.

08:49.596 --> 08:49.928
Hey.

08:49.930 --> 08:53.198
Don't ever put your happiness in anyone else's hands.

08:53.200 --> 08:55.667
You hear me?

08:55.669 --> 08:56.835
I'll drop it.

08:56.837 --> 08:58.970
I'll drop it every time.

09:02.608 --> 09:03.808
Bye!

09:21.294 --> 09:23.161
♪♪ (Eerie music)

09:23.163 --> 09:26.798
(Dog barking)

09:55.027 --> 09:57.329
(Linda) Oh, my babies.

10:00.633 --> 10:02.300
Just rest, mom.

10:03.603 --> 10:04.936
You're okay.

10:05.771 --> 10:07.906
They said you were gonna be okay.

10:07.908 --> 10:09.908
I know they did, honey.

10:16.148 --> 10:17.682
Aaron.

10:17.684 --> 10:19.651
Baby, look at me.

10:19.653 --> 10:23.855
You're gonna have to cover my shift tomorrow night, okay?

10:30.863 --> 10:33.198
(Sighs)

10:34.200 --> 10:36.267
We're gonna be fine.

10:39.038 --> 10:40.639
You'll see.

10:42.108 --> 10:46.111
♪♪ (Soft music)

10:46.113 --> 10:48.113
(Teacher) Latham?

10:48.115 --> 10:50.048
(Latham) Here.

10:50.050 --> 10:50.715
Leeds.

10:50.717 --> 10:52.183
(Leeds) Here.

10:52.185 --> 10:53.051
Long.

10:53.053 --> 10:54.953
(Long) Here.

10:54.955 --> 10:56.421
Marks.

10:57.723 --> 10:59.791
Oh, dear.

10:59.793 --> 11:01.159
Excuse me.

11:02.261 --> 11:04.162
McCormick.

11:05.264 --> 11:06.264
Here.

11:06.266 --> 11:09.334
(Phone rings)

11:11.070 --> 11:12.037
(Linda) Okay.

11:12.039 --> 11:14.773
(Ringing continues)

11:15.841 --> 11:17.308
(Adam) All right.

11:21.013 --> 11:22.881
Hello?

11:24.150 --> 11:25.450
Yeah.

11:26.819 --> 11:29.087
Stop calling here.

11:29.089 --> 11:29.821
Who is it?

11:29.823 --> 11:31.423
The crazy bitch that hit you?

11:31.425 --> 11:33.958
She doesn't want to talk to you!

11:35.061 --> 11:35.694
Yeah.

11:35.696 --> 11:37.328
What do you think she wants?

11:37.330 --> 11:38.697
She's a little busy right now,

11:38.699 --> 11:42.300
considering you just ran her over with your van.

11:47.039 --> 11:49.808
(Gracie) So what took you so long?

11:49.810 --> 11:51.209
(Adam) Sorry.

11:51.211 --> 11:52.711
I ran.

11:55.114 --> 11:56.715
(Chuckles)

11:56.717 --> 11:57.982
Come on.

12:02.254 --> 12:09.027
♪♪ (Ambient rock)

12:10.296 --> 12:13.832
(Gracie) Don't just stand there, come in.

12:24.243 --> 12:25.076
How's your drink?

12:25.078 --> 12:27.445
Did I make it too strong?

12:37.389 --> 12:40.225
You've got quite a collection.

12:42.194 --> 12:46.097
I... I didn't know rocks could be so beautiful.

12:48.234 --> 12:49.501
I know.

12:54.039 --> 12:55.340
Sit down.

13:10.422 --> 13:13.458
I, uh, like your shelves.

13:13.460 --> 13:14.259
Thanks.

13:14.261 --> 13:16.394
My dad made them for me.

13:26.438 --> 13:27.272
(Sighs)

13:27.274 --> 13:30.275
I see graves all the time now.

13:44.123 --> 13:46.991
Beds are kinda like graves.

13:51.931 --> 13:54.866
What kind of funeral do you want?

13:58.070 --> 14:00.238
Aren't they all the same?

14:00.240 --> 14:03.374
No, they're all completely different.

14:03.376 --> 14:06.511
In Mexico, on Day of the Dead,

14:06.513 --> 14:08.379
the families go to the cemeteries

14:08.381 --> 14:11.216
and picnic on the graves of a loved one.

14:11.218 --> 14:13.184
They burn incense to guide the way

14:13.186 --> 14:16.120
between the road of the dead and the living.

14:16.122 --> 14:18.957
Is that what you were doing the other day?

14:40.045 --> 14:42.280
I think you should go now.

14:46.418 --> 14:47.919
Okay.

14:51.523 --> 14:55.026
Don't worry, you're invited back.

14:57.429 --> 14:58.897
Oh.

15:05.504 --> 15:08.606
Thanks for showing me your rocks.

15:29.929 --> 15:31.496
(Aaron) Not today, bro.

15:31.498 --> 15:33.498
You're on your own.

15:33.500 --> 15:34.098
Come on.

15:34.100 --> 15:36.467
Sorry, we got important shit to attend to.

15:36.469 --> 15:37.568
(Girl snickering)

15:37.570 --> 15:38.303
Yeah, like what?

15:38.305 --> 15:40.972
(Brunette) Aaron's taking us to where they found him.

15:40.974 --> 15:42.206
(Blonde) You should come, Adam.

15:42.208 --> 15:43.374
Jenny Miller says she saw him

15:43.376 --> 15:46.010
hanging around by the bridge down there.

15:46.012 --> 15:48.479
No thanks.

15:48.481 --> 15:50.448
It's not a circus.

15:50.450 --> 15:52.116
What'd you just say?

15:52.118 --> 15:52.684
Let's just go.

15:52.686 --> 15:55.386
Why do you give a shit what we do?

15:57.623 --> 16:00.325
(Engine starting)

16:16.375 --> 16:18.576
(Lucy) I think it's about...

16:18.578 --> 16:20.011
(Cries)

16:20.013 --> 16:21.980
Seven months.

16:23.482 --> 16:24.716
(Linda) I understand.

16:24.718 --> 16:27.051
I think it was about...

16:27.053 --> 16:30.154
That one night, I had to...

16:30.156 --> 16:32.023
(Door opening)

16:32.025 --> 16:33.057
Adam?

16:33.059 --> 16:34.559
Honey, is that you?

16:34.561 --> 16:35.426
Yeah.

16:35.428 --> 16:37.595
Come in here a minute.

16:39.665 --> 16:41.232
What's up?

16:45.738 --> 16:47.505
What is she doing here?

16:47.507 --> 16:49.240
Adam, what happened wasn't Lucy's fault.

16:49.242 --> 16:50.708
- It was an accident.
- Of course it was her fault.

16:50.710 --> 16:53.244
She's my friend, I want you to be nice to her.

16:53.246 --> 16:56.280
- Since when?
- Adam, I know this is really tough for you.

16:56.282 --> 16:58.683
I know there's been so much going on, but...

16:58.685 --> 17:00.251
Oh, you gotta be fucking kidding me.

17:00.253 --> 17:03.521
It's... it's so awful what happened to that Marks boy,

17:03.523 --> 17:06.190
and... and... and if you need to talk...

17:06.192 --> 17:09.460
Just stay out of it, “Paralyzer”.

17:09.462 --> 17:11.662
Adam.

17:11.664 --> 17:13.064
Mom.

17:13.066 --> 17:16.267
She is the reason you're in this wheelchair.

17:16.269 --> 17:18.368
She hit you head-on, she was drunk...

17:18.371 --> 17:20.371
I wasn't drunk, it was an accident.

17:20.373 --> 17:22.339
- Yeah, a drunk accident.
- You know that.

17:22.342 --> 17:23.441
It... I wasn't drunk.

17:23.443 --> 17:24.375
Just go away.

17:24.377 --> 17:25.742
Lucy's just trying to help.

17:25.744 --> 17:27.678
You apologize to her this instant.

17:27.680 --> 17:30.348
Apologize for what?

17:30.350 --> 17:31.215
We are not the only ones

17:31.217 --> 17:33.084
who've had tragedy touch our lives.

17:33.086 --> 17:36.587
Fate brings people together for a reason.

17:38.057 --> 17:40.291
What does that even mean?

17:41.794 --> 17:44.128
There's some chili on the stove.

17:44.130 --> 17:46.497
Will you put it in bowls for us?

17:47.533 --> 17:49.233
Why can't The Paralyzer do it?

17:49.235 --> 17:52.236
Lucy made the chili, Adam.

17:53.338 --> 17:56.541
Did you know Adam was born prematurely?

17:56.742 --> 17:59.844
With underdeveloped lungs and a murmur in his heart?

17:59.846 --> 18:01.112
- Really?
- Yeah.

18:01.114 --> 18:03.181
Oh, that's so scary.

18:08.687 --> 18:11.689
My parents are gone until 10 tonight.

18:11.691 --> 18:13.291
I mean, if you wanna come over.

18:13.293 --> 18:16.727
<i>(Jamie's mother) I never had to worry about him doing things</i>

18:16.729 --> 18:18.529
<i>that he wasn't supposed to.</i>

18:18.531 --> 18:23.534
<i>He was a... a scout, and always on a project.</i>

18:23.536 --> 18:24.702
<i>I'll tell you this much.</i>

18:24.704 --> 18:28.339
<i>Some sick pervert murdered my boy,</i>

18:28.341 --> 18:31.476
<i>and God's vengeance needs to be carried out,</i>

18:31.478 --> 18:33.611
<i>so Jamie won't have died in va...</i>

18:33.613 --> 18:34.645
(Radio clicks off)

18:34.647 --> 18:36.447
What a load of crap.

18:36.449 --> 18:38.549
So what if they find out what happened to him?

18:38.551 --> 18:42.520
I mean, it's not gonna make things meaningful.

18:42.522 --> 18:44.222
What do you mean?

18:45.224 --> 18:46.858
He's still dead.

18:46.860 --> 18:47.859
Big fucking deal.

18:47.861 --> 18:50.695
It won't change his story.

18:53.866 --> 18:55.299
Sorry.

18:57.503 --> 19:00.471
You don't have to be sorry.

19:05.677 --> 19:08.746
Can we please not talk about him?

19:22.594 --> 19:26.531
(Heavy breathing and sighing)

19:33.605 --> 19:35.640
(Gracie sighs)

19:50.656 --> 19:53.824
I think that he should've been loved,

19:54.927 --> 19:57.328
though...

20:01.733 --> 20:03.834
He never got that.

20:06.805 --> 20:09.340
Not like how everyone deserves.

20:09.342 --> 20:15.846
♪♪ (Tense music)

20:17.316 --> 20:19.317
What are you looking at?

20:19.319 --> 20:20.718
Nothing.

20:21.386 --> 20:24.288
Look, do you want another drink?

20:24.290 --> 20:26.424
Uh, yeah, sure.

20:26.426 --> 20:27.625
Hey.

20:29.361 --> 20:30.728
Come here.

20:32.331 --> 20:34.365
Adam.

20:35.901 --> 20:38.002
Don't.

20:38.004 --> 20:39.470
Gracie.

20:42.274 --> 20:45.843
Look, just pretend like you don't see him.

20:50.515 --> 20:53.618
But I do see him.

20:53.620 --> 20:56.254
(Breathes heavily)

20:58.490 --> 20:59.757
What does he want?

20:59.759 --> 21:00.925
How the fuck should I know?

21:00.927 --> 21:04.662
Can... come on, can we please just drop this?

21:04.664 --> 21:07.732
Look, I did not choose for him to be here.

21:07.734 --> 21:09.867
I found him, but not because I wanted to.

21:09.869 --> 21:12.970
You're acting like I asked for this.

21:12.972 --> 21:13.971
Look, I'm sorry, I was just...

21:13.973 --> 21:16.574
Adam, I don't want a dead boy

21:16.576 --> 21:20.811
lurking around outside of my house, okay?

21:23.282 --> 21:24.582
Okay?

21:29.021 --> 21:30.521
And...

21:32.624 --> 21:33.991
trust me,

21:35.560 --> 21:37.662
neither do you.

21:37.664 --> 21:44.001
♪♪

22:16.702 --> 22:19.403
(Jamie) What are you waiting for?

22:27.379 --> 22:28.713
You're not real.

22:28.715 --> 22:30.948
Don't be frightened.

22:31.850 --> 22:34.051
I don't wanna hurt you.

22:35.654 --> 22:37.588
I'm not frightened.

22:39.024 --> 22:41.425
You can call me Mooney.

22:44.629 --> 22:47.565
Everybody does.

22:49.935 --> 22:52.470
I never liked that name.

22:54.940 --> 22:56.941
Me neither.

23:00.812 --> 23:03.047
I won't call you that then.

23:07.152 --> 23:09.153
Thank you, Adam.

23:16.661 --> 23:20.431
I never thought anybody would be able to see me.

23:21.600 --> 23:22.900
I see you.

23:26.438 --> 23:28.706
Gracie can too, I think.

23:33.011 --> 23:35.846
She's just scared.

23:46.057 --> 23:48.092
Don't be shy.

23:52.164 --> 23:55.065
I know you wanna try it.

23:55.067 --> 23:57.001
Try what?

24:03.141 --> 24:05.943
Take off your clothes first.

24:16.755 --> 24:18.122
Go ahead.

24:57.195 --> 24:59.497
Get in.

25:50.682 --> 25:52.182
Close your eyes.

25:57.889 --> 26:00.057
Can you help me, Adam?

26:04.563 --> 26:05.763
Yes.

26:10.135 --> 26:11.635
I knew it.

26:11.637 --> 26:14.238
I knew it would be you.

26:21.813 --> 26:24.615
(Girls giggling)

26:24.617 --> 26:25.749
(Aaron) What the fuck?

26:25.751 --> 26:26.984
(Girl) Isn't that...

26:26.986 --> 26:27.818
Why are you naked?

26:27.820 --> 26:29.687
(Aaron) Get the fuck outta there!

26:29.689 --> 26:32.990
Put your fucking pants on, for Christ's sake.

26:32.992 --> 26:39.763
♪♪ (Hard rock)

26:50.675 --> 26:53.611
They both knocked, but they can't come in.

26:53.613 --> 26:56.914
(Both laugh)

26:56.916 --> 26:58.015
Oh, my God.

26:58.017 --> 26:58.916
Adam?

26:58.918 --> 27:01.685
Adam, honey, are you okay?

27:01.687 --> 27:04.321
Why are you naked?

27:04.323 --> 27:06.023
What happened?

28:09.754 --> 28:10.988
Hello?

28:33.144 --> 28:34.411
Hi.

28:39.317 --> 28:41.452
What are you doing in there?

28:43.154 --> 28:44.888
Why are you all wet?

28:45.924 --> 28:47.324
I'm sorry.

28:50.261 --> 28:51.862
Don't be sorry.

28:55.066 --> 28:57.067
Where are your clothes?

29:02.173 --> 29:04.141
I don't have any.

29:27.532 --> 29:28.966
Here.

29:33.471 --> 29:35.239
Are you sure?

29:36.341 --> 29:37.908
I'm sure.

29:38.343 --> 29:41.345
- Really?
- Yes, really, put on...

29:44.082 --> 29:45.449
Thank you.

30:21.886 --> 30:23.086
Wow.

30:25.356 --> 30:27.324
Your room's nice.

30:43.074 --> 30:44.441
What happened?

30:46.845 --> 30:48.245
I mean, really.

30:50.114 --> 30:51.348
Dead?

30:52.917 --> 30:54.384
Right?

30:54.386 --> 30:56.553
Don't worry about me.

30:58.890 --> 31:00.257
Who did it?

31:01.626 --> 31:05.028
Don't ask me that, please don't ask me that.

31:05.030 --> 31:07.130
Why not?

31:07.132 --> 31:08.966
Right?

31:08.968 --> 31:10.500
I can help you.

31:10.502 --> 31:12.102
Help them track down whoever did...

31:12.104 --> 31:13.470
It was...

31:15.874 --> 31:17.307
It was awful.

31:20.178 --> 31:22.946
That's all you need to know.

31:36.294 --> 31:38.428
Or you can help me.

31:42.133 --> 31:43.333
How?

31:46.938 --> 31:49.039
Give me something.

31:51.109 --> 31:52.242
What?

31:52.244 --> 31:53.977
A word.

31:54.679 --> 31:56.980
Whisper it to me.

31:59.250 --> 32:00.684
What kind of word?

32:02.287 --> 32:04.321
It doesn't matter.

32:04.323 --> 32:06.523
It could be anything.

32:13.398 --> 32:15.365
(Sniffles)

32:43.428 --> 32:44.695
Murder.

32:58.142 --> 33:01.645
(Breathes heavily)

33:09.354 --> 33:10.220
(Linda pounding on door)

33:10.222 --> 33:13.156
Honey, there's a call for you!

33:15.560 --> 33:17.027
Hello?

33:17.029 --> 33:18.362
Uh, who is it?

